- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the dynamics of social groups in social networks and proposes a new method for exploring their evolution.
- cs.SD (Software Development and Programming) is also likely as the paper describes a new algorithm for analyzing social network data.
- cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) is relevant as the paper deals with social groups and their evolution.
- cs.DB (Databases) is relevant as the paper discusses the storage and analysis of social network data.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions the potential use of the proposed method in human resource management and marketing, which could involve AI techniques.
